^B@2^*BHoward Schutzman: ^*N|cp||at|Cohen correctly asserts that most people who play 2 over 1 game forcing treat a 2@C response to 1@D as game forcing. However, I personally do not like to play that. I prefer that 2@C over 1@D has the same meaning as if you were playing SAYC -- 10+ points and 5+ clubs (e.g. it only promises an invitational hand). Otherwise you have an awkward time bidding invitational hands with clubs when partner opens 1@D. The reason this problem exists is because 1NT forcing is not available over 1@D.|
